 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-7: Implement task title pyramid — generate_title_levels() producing L0/L1/L2 summaries at task creation (INV-INTERFACE-008, ADR-BUDGET-006). BACKGROUND: Task titles are the single biggest source of token bloat. A typical task title is 200+ chars (~50 tokens). With 300+ tasks, listing them consumes 15,000+ tokens. The title pyramid pre-computes multi-resolution summaries: L0 (~4 words, e.g. 'CALM classification'), L1 (~12 words, e.g. 'TOPO-CALM: CALM classification of task phases'), L2 (~25 words, first sentence of title). These are stored as attributes on the task entity: :task/title-l0, :task/title-l1 (L2 = existing :task/title truncated to first sentence). Generation: (1) Extract title prefix (before first colon or dash), (2) L0 = first 2-3 significant words after prefix, (3) L1 = prefix + L0 + key qualifiers, (4) L2 = first sentence. The levels are computed at task creation time and stored as datoms — zero cost at query time. APPROACH: (1) Add :task/title-l0 and :task/title-l1 schema attributes. (2) Add generate_title_levels(title) -> (String, String) to task.rs. (3) Wire into create_task_datoms(). (4) Backfill: add backfill_title_levels(store) for existing tasks. Tests: (A) L0 is <= 25 chars. (B) L1 is <= 80 chars. (C) L0 is a substring of L1. (D) generate_title_levels is deterministic. (E) PREFIX: pattern extraction works for 'TOPO-CALM:', 'BOUNDARY-1:', 'CRB-6:' prefixes. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/task.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs"
